article.headline: Belmont 46, Air Force 38
article.story: NASHVILLE, (AP) -- Adam Mark scored 24 points to lead Belmont to a 46-38 victory Sunday over Air Force. Mark scored seven points in a 10-0 second half run that gave Belmont (3-1) control of the game. He scored a total of 18 points in the second half. Mark scored a 3-pointer with 5:46 left to give Belmont an eight-point lead. Air Force (2-1) would get no closer than six points the rest of the game. Belmont hit six of nine free throws in the closing minutes to seal the win. Joel Gerlach and Nick Welch each scored nine points for Air Force. Air Force, which made just 14-of-40 shots from the floor, led 15-12 at halftime.
